                                                      Harwinder wins gold in 20km walk  Kochi: Harwinder Singh of Services came up with extra energy in the last lap of the 20km walk to clinch the gold medal in the 48th National Open Athletic Championship on the penultimate day here on Wednesday.  Harwinder, a Havildar with Army Ordnance Corps, Secunderabad, was close on the heels of Ashok Kumar Patel of Railway till the last lap. But Harwinder picked up speed and with 300 metres to go for the finish he took the lead and maintained it successfully to win the gold with a time of 1 hour 35.21 seconds.  Marathon  New Delhi: The fourth edition of the Airtel Delhi Half Marathon will be held on November 9, it was announced by Indian Olympic Association President Suresh Kalmadi here on Tuesday.  ITF tourney  New Delhi: Prajnesh Gunneswaran marched into the quarter finals of the $15,000 ITF tournament, outplaying compatriot Ronak Manuja even as reigning national grass court champion Vishnu Vardhan made his exit after losing his second round match here on Wednesday.  Doping  Beijing: The Paralympics suffered its second doping scandal in as many days on Wednesday, with a German basketballer debarred from participating for taking a banned drug contained in hair loss treatment.  BCCI says no  New Delhi: The Board of Control for Cricket in India on Wednesday rejected the plan to hold the Champions Trophy in October 2009 because the dates would clash with India rsquo;s home ODI series against Australia.  According to a website, BCCI made their opposition to the Champions Trophy dates in ICC rsquo;s chief executives meeting and the matter will be discussed in the ICC Board meeting on Thursday.  Play called off  Hyderabad: The second day rsquo;s play in the three-day match between India lsquo;A rsquo; and the Australians on Wednesday was called off without a ball being bowled because of rain.  SLC elections  Colombo: Sri Lanka rsquo;s cricket board is set for its first elections in 